<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="tough-adj">tough <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /tʌf/    美 /tʌf/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-weak">1.★ <strong>强壮的【反:weak】;坚强的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you sure you’re physically tough enough for this job?
你确定你的身体足够强壮能应付这份工作吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He plays the <strong>tough guy</strong> in the movie. 
他在电影中扮演硬汉。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>结实的；坚固的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a tough pair of shoes
一双结实的鞋子</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(食物等) 嚼不烂的；老的</strong></h4>
<p>反 tender  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The meat was tough and hard to chew. 
这肉太老，很难嚼动。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>强硬的; 严厉的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t be too <strong>tough on / with</strong> him — he was only a child. 
别对他要求过严，他只是个孩子。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>艰苦的；艰难的；棘手的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a tough match / job 
艰苦的比赛/棘手的工作</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is tough to make a decision. 
很难作决定。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>toughen /'tʌfn/ v <br />
toughly /tʌfli/ adv <br />
toughness /tʌfnəs/ n [U]  </p></div>